==English==
===Noun===
'''element'''  (''plural'' '''[[elements]]''')

#{{chemistry}}  Any one of the simplest [[chemical]] substances that cannot be [[decompose]]d in a [[chemical reaction]] and made up of [[atom]]s all having the same number of [[proton]]s.
# One of the four basic building blocks of [[matter]] in theories of ancient [[philosopher]]s and [[alchemist]]s: water, earth, fire, and air.
# Something small.
#:''an element of doubt''
# A place or state of being that an individual or object is better suited towards.
#:''be in one's own element''
#{{law}} A necessary aspect or component of an action to be considered a certain type of crime by law.<!--repetition:  All of the legal aspects specified by law must be committed or present for an action to be considered a violation of the law and must be proven at a criminal trial for a conviction.-->
#{{settheory}} One of the objects in a [[set]].
#A group of people within a larger group having a particular common characteristic.
#:''You sometimes find the hooligan element at football matches.''
#A component in electrical equipment, often in the form of a coil, having a high [[resistance]], thereby generating heat when a current is passed through it.
#:''The element in this electric kettle can heat the water in under a minute.''

